</td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: BST epic</span><hr size=1> Moltenfists: the Enchanter epic can't be multiquested past the first step (out of 5), because the last four steps require combining items in a bag (and then combining the four resulting items in ANOTHER bag).  So, you can't multiquest more than 2 out of the 19 parts.<br>
<br>
Someone said on this board earlier that the person developing the BST epic is the same person who made the Enchanter and Druid (and Ranger?) epics.  So, it probably requires you to obtain a couple dozen random items.<br>
<br>
My bet: it'll require Kunark but not Velious.  By this point, Kunark can be considered part of the &quot;old world&quot; like Odus, Antonica, and Faydwer; for evidence, note that there's a portal in the Nexus going to Kunark (and the big Dreadlands spires are now part of the Luclin story), while there isn't one for Velious.  So, I think it's fair game for the BST epic.  Plus, there are Iksar Beastlords.<br>
<br>
But, since (according to the manual) the entire concept for the Beastlord class was a Vah Shir invention that other &quot;primitive&quot; races adopted, it'd make sense that large parts of the quest would be on Luclin, especially the starting point. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urisca138.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Risca138</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/10/02 12:43:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3584.topic&index=102>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: BST epic</span><hr size=1> It was stated earlier that the BST Epic may involve the the claws quests for the Vah Shir. This does not make any sense to me. For one the Acrylia Slate for citizenship can only be obtained by Vah Shir or MQ but is not really meant for non Vah Shir also the Claws are Vah Shir only. I could see if all the races had similar quests and and eventually you would need said item like the Monk headband/sashs that would make sense. As far as I know and may be wrong there are no such quests for non Vah Shir BST's. Furthermore the particle weapon quests are part of the Kunark Expansion. Much like the Wild Lords armor that only drops on Kunark it is just my opinion that the BST epic will have little or nothing to do with Luclin itself. Then again I could be wrong but just dropping my 2 cp<br>
